To help support FPC in this, and many other efforts to protect and expand the right to keep and bear arms, please consider joining the FPC Grassroots Army by visiting JoinFPC.org

node.title: FPC files lawsuit against Nevada's AB 286 banning home built firearms

Bonta to explain why this case is as important as it is, and how FPC and co-plaintiffs managed to defeat the State of California's tyrannical Assault Weapons Control Act.

Unfortunately, Attorney General Bonta has already expressed a desire to appeal the ruling, meaning that we still need your help! To join the Grassroots Army and help take this case all the way to the Supreme Court, please visit JoinFPC.org. Likewise, to stay up-to-date on the Miller case in particular, stay tuned to AssaultWeaponLawsuit.com.

FPC's Matt Larosiere sits down and explains the ins and outs of the ATF's Proposed Rule 2021R-08, a rule change which would all but ban the legal use of pistol braces. The new rule contains a huge degree of vague and uncertain principles, combined with an absurd and illogical "points system" and a clause giving the ATF power to rule against their own criteria if they so choose!

This new rule is a slap in the face of gun owners, and we can't afford for it to go into effect. Unfortunately, the ATF is not yet allowing comments on their new proposed rule – though comments will open in the near future. To stay up-to-date, and to take action once comments are live, please visit SaveTheBraces.com. Likewise, to join the FPC Grassroots Army and fight back against tyranny and executive overreach, go to JoinFPC.org.

node.title: Decoding the ATF's proposed BAN on pistol braces

node.text:
The ATF has just released Proposed Rule 2021R-08, which would reclassify millions of braced pistols as NFA-defined Short Barrel Rifles (SBRs). Much like the ATF's new receiver rule (2021R-05), this new rule greatly expands ATF power at the expense of your right to keep and bear arms. Furthermore, this new rule would make millions of law-abiding gun owners into felons overnight, thanks to backroom administrative lawmaking.

While the ATF announced the rule today, they have no yet opened the rule for comment. Stay tuned to SaveTheBraces.com for the most up-to-date news, where we will include a link to comment on the proposed rule as soon as the ATF publishes it. While you're at it, please also visit FightATF.com to fight back against the ATF's propsed rule on braces, and FightChipman.com to demand your senator vote "No" on Waco Dave's nomination to lead the corrupt ATF.
